Detectives have arrested two Kenyans and a Ugandan man for allegedly defrauding Kenyan saccos of millions of shillings. Mr Gabantu Patrick Emmanuel (Ugandan) and Kenyans Zahra Ahmed and Abdullazac Rajab are accused of defrauding Safaricom, Bamburi, Stima and other saccos Several passports in their possession have been recovered, the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI Kenya) said in its official Twitter page.